{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771944041,"nonce":"PBsmX6KhwkK6KeR4rtb/GZOpx38=","title":"Add observation normalization (running mean/std) for RL training and as graph component","message":"## Context\n\nRL training of musculoskeletal controllers requires observation normalization (running mean/std) for stable learning. This is standard in PPO/SAC but feedbax currently has no normalization support.\n\n## Design Requirements\n\n### Two-layer architecture\n\n1. **Core logic** (pure functions): `RunningNormState` (count, mean, var via Welford's algorithm), `update_stats(state, batch)`, `normalize(state, obs, eps, clip)`. Not tied to either pipeline.\n\n2. **Graph Component** (`ObsNormalizer`): Wraps core logic as a `Component` with input/output ports and `StateIndex` for running stats. Insertable via `graph.insert_between()`. Lives in `components.py` alongside Gain, Saturation, etc.\n\n3. **RL pipeline integration**: Normalizer state carried alongside `opt_state` in PPO training loop. Applied in `_collect_rollout` after computing obs. Updated with batch statistics after each rollout. For `train_ppo_batched`, normalizer state has shape `(B, obs_dim)` for per-body normalization, vmapped alongside everything else.\n\n### Per-variable configuration\n\nDefault: automatic standardization. Per-slice overrides:\n- Joint positions/velocities: `standardize` (vary across body morphologies)\n- Muscle activations: `passthrough` or `scale` to [0,1] (already bounded)\n- Effector/target position: `standardize` (workspace-dependent)\n- Target velocity: `standardize`\n- Phase: `passthrough` (already in [0,1])\n\nSupported modes: `standardize`, `passthrough`, `scale` (fixed range), `angle`/`phase`.\n\n### Training/eval toggle\n\nUse `eqx.tree_at` to set a `training` field to False, which gates `lax.cond` on stat updates. Consider warm-up period (1-2 rollouts) to seed statistics before training.\n\n### Batch statistics merging\n\nFor vmapped envs/bodies, use Welford parallel merge to correctly combine per-environment statistics.\n\n## Codex recommendation\n\nCodex (GPT-5.2) recommended Option A (standalone Component) as primary, citing: graph composition is the core abstraction, Component-owned StateIndex is the natural home for running stats, and insert_between() exists precisely for this use case.\n\n## References\n\n- Standard in all successful musculoskeletal RL (MyoSuite, DEP-RL, LATTICE)\n- Related to issue about RL/OC UI integration (see companion issue)","files":null}]}